text: Natalie C. J. Strynadka FRS is a professor of Biochemistry in the Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology at the University of British Columbia. ==Education== Strynadka was educated at the University of Alberta where she was awarded a PhD in 1990. Her thesis committee included Michael N. G. James and Sir David Chilton Phillips. ==Awards and honours== Strynadka was elected a Fellow of the Royal Society (FRS) in 2015.
